request.description:
shh_version
Returns the current semver version number.

Parameters
none

Returns
String - The version number.

Example
// Request
curl -X POST --data '{
"jsonrpc":"2.0",
"method":"shh_version",
"params":[],
"id":1
}'

// Result
{
  "id":1,
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "result": "6.0"
}

shh_newKeyPair
Generates a new public and private key pair for message decryption and encryption.

Parameters
none

Returns
String: Key ID on success and an error on failure.

Example
// Request
curl -X POST --data '{
"jsonrpc":"2.0",
"method":"shh_newKeyPair",
"id":1
}'

// Result
{
  "id":1,
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "result": "5e57b9ffc2387e18636e0a3d0c56b023264c16e78a2adcba1303cefc685e610f"
}

shh_deleteKeyPair
Deletes the specifies key if it exists.

Parameters
String: ID of key pair.
Returns
Boolean: true on success and an error on failure.

Example
// Request
curl -X POST --data '{
"jsonrpc":"2.0",
"method":"shh_deleteKeyPair",
"params":["5e57b9ffc2387e18636e0a3d0c56b023264c16e78a2adcba1303cefc685e610f"],
"id":1
	
}'

// Result
{
  "id":1,
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "result": true
}

shh_hasKeyPair
Checks if the whisper node has a private key of a key pair matching the given ID.

Parameters
String: ID of key pair.
Returns
Boolean: (true or false) and error on failure.

Example
// Request
curl -X POST --data '{
"jsonrpc":"2.0",
"method":"shh_hasKeyPair",
"params":["5e57b9ffc2387e18636e0a3d0c56b023264c16e78a2adcba1303cefc685e610f"],
"id":1
	
}'

// Result
{
  "id":1,
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "result": false
}

shh_getPublicKey
Returns the public key for identity ID.

Parameters
String: ID of key pair.
Returns
String: Public key on success and an error on failure.

Example
// Request
curl -X POST --data '{
"jsonrpc":"2.0",
"method":"shh_getPublicKey",
"params":["86e658cbc6da63120b79b5eec0c67d5dcfb6865a8f983eff08932477282b77bb"],
"id":1
	
}'

// Result
{
  "id":1,
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "result": "0x04d1574d4eab8f3dde4d2dc7ed2c4d699d77cbbdd09167b8fffa099652ce4df00c4c6e0263eafe05007a46fdf0c8d32b11aeabcd3abbc7b2bc2bb967368a68e9c6"
}

shh_getPrivateKey
Returns the private key for identity ID.

Parameters
String: ID of the key pair.
Returns
String: Private key on success and an error on failure.

Example
// Request
curl -X POST --data '{
"jsonrpc":"2.0",
"method":"shh_getPrivateKey",
"params":["0xc862bf3cf4565d46abcbadaf4712a8940bfea729a91b9b0e338eab5166341ab5"],
"id":1
	
}'

// Result
{
  "id":1,
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "result": "0x234234e22b9ffc2387e18636e0534534a3d0c56b0243567432453264c16e78a2adc"
}

shh_newSymKey
Generates a random symmetric key and stores it under an ID, which is then returned. Can be used encrypting and decrypting messages where the key is known to both parties.

Parameters
none

Returns
String: Key ID on success and an error on failure.

Example
// Request
curl -X POST --data '{
"jsonrpc":"2.0",
"method":"shh_newSymKey", 
"params": [], 
"id":1
}'

// Result
{
  "id":1,
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "result": "cec94d139ff51d7df1d228812b90c23ec1f909afa0840ed80f1e04030bb681e4"
}

shh_generateSymKeyFromPassword
Generates the key from password, stores it, and returns its ID.

Parameters
String: password.
Returns
String: Key ID on success and an error on failure.

Example
// Request
curl -X POST --data '{
"jsonrpc":"2.0",
"method":"shh_generateSymKeyFromPassword",
"params":["test"],
"id":1
}'

// Result
{
  "id":1,
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "result": "2e57b9ffc2387e18636e0a3d0c56b023264c16e78a2adcba1303cefc685e610f"
}

shh_hasSymKey
Returns true if there is a key associated with the name string. Otherwise, returns false.

Parameters
String: key ID.
Returns
Boolean (true or false) on success and an error on failure.

Example
// Request
curl -X POST --data '{
"jsonrpc":"2.0",
"method":"shh_hasSymKey",
"params":["f6dcf21ed6a17bd78d8c4c63195ab997b3b65ea683705501eae82d32667adc92"],
"id":1
}'

// Result
{
  "id":1,
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "result": true
}

shh_unsubscribe
Cancels and removes an existing subscription.

Parameters
String: subscription ID.
Returns
Boolean: true or false.

Example
// Request
curl -X POST --data '{
"jsonrpc":"2.0",
"method":"shh_unsubscribe",
"params":["02c1f5c953804acee3b68eda6c0afe3f1b4e0bec73c7445e10d45da333616412"],
"id":1
}'

// Result
{
  "id":1,
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "result": true
}

shh_newMessageFilter
Create a new filter within the node. This filter can be used to poll for new messages that match the set of criteria.

Parameters
criteria - Object: see shh_subscribe
Returns
String: filter identifier

Example
// Request
curl -X POST --data '{
"jsonrpc":"2.0",
"method":"shh_newMessageFilter",
"params":[{
"symKeyID": "3742c75e4232325d54143707e4b73d17c2f86a5e4abe3359021be5653f5b2c81"
}],
"id":1
}' 

// Result
{"jsonrpc":"2.0","id":1,"result":"2b47fbafb3cce24570812a82e6e93cd9e2551bbc4823f6548ff0d82d2206b326"}
